# gen212 (cardinal KB-first principle, OUTPUT side): the agent's reply phrasings are KB
# knowledge (response_template/2 in kb/core/responses.p0), filled by kb_response, and the
# class of phrasings GROWS at runtime. Here parrot0 is taught a new greeting wording and
# the next name it learns is welcomed with it — kb_response rotates over the registered
# phrasings, so the base form and the taught form alternate (the gen55 anti-repeat
# instinct). The OUTPUT mirror of intent_learn.chat's input side; no code edit either.
> my name is Ada
< Nice to meet you, Ada!
> greet new names with "Welcome, {name}!"
< Got it - I'll greet new names with "Welcome, {name}!" too now.
> my name is Bob
< Welcome, Bob!
